================================================================================
REVIEWED SUMMARY
================================================================================

C++ header:         (none — .cpp only)
C++ implementation: src/emTreeDump/emTreeDumpFpPlugin.cpp

Purpose: emFpPlugin entry point (extern "C" emTreeDumpFpPluginFunc)
that registers emTreeDumpFilePanel with Eagle Mode's file-panel
plugin system so that opening a .emTreeDump file in the running app
constructs an emTreeDumpFilePanel bound to an emTreeDumpFileModel for
that path. The glue that wires the file extension into the in-app
renderer.

Status: NOT PORTED — in-app dump-renderer subsystem out of scope for
the current dump-producer work (Phase 1 of
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-24-treedump-port-design.md).

A plugin that constructs emTreeDumpFilePanel is meaningless until
emTreeDumpFilePanel exists in the Rust port. Nothing to register.

Rust equivalent for now: none.

Future port path: ports together with emTreeDumpFilePanel and
emTreeDumpFileModel — the last piece, registering the assembled
renderer with the Rust port's emFpPlugin machinery so .emTreeDump
files open in the viewer.
